##72 hours, all recorded. I was on the k-3 to witness the "transnational epidemic. "

New-weekly

Function Introduction "new weekly" was first published on August 18,1996, and was sponsored by Southern Publishing Media Co. , Ltd. . With the orientation of "China's newest and cutting-edge lifestyle weekly" , it published a series of special reports with great influence, it is one of the most representative and influential magazines in China's periodical market, and enjoys the reputation of "topic source" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The famous K3 train

The K3 train is like a small boat that passes calmly through the eye of a new type of pneumonia storm. It seems completely isolated from the critical epidemic situation in China, but it is constantly being buffeted by information and public opinion concerning its own fate.

As the virus rampaged through Wuhan, my family and I boarded K3, a train from China to Moscow, and we dreamed of a trip across Asia and Europe, unaware of the gravity of what had happened in that city.

Meanwhile, cocoa was on the K3, holding a bouquet of lavender daisies. She wiped the dirty window-pane in front of her several times with a Napkin, then stuck the daisies in it.

"there will be snow and Birch trees outside. Wow, beautiful pictures. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In reality, the journey is not always as happy as in the movies. / The movie Mama Jon

Cocoa, a Shanghai girl I met after Boarding K3, was the first picture I took of her on the K3 train, holding a daisy. I didn't realize that for the next 72 hours, my camera wouldn't have the chance to see how the romantic images from the Russian literature would come alive, but inadvertently recorded a real "Odyssey. ".

At 2010 hours on January 22, the K3 train stopped at Erlian station at the sino-mongolian border station on time. Passengers wrapped up their down jackets, rushed to the temperature of minus 11 degrees platform, and green car body on the national emblem for a photo.

Perhaps it was New Year's Eve approaching, through the glass doors of the entrance hall, you can see the shops across the street closed early. The only thing worth recording with a camera is the "long live the solidarity of the world" Neon sign on the side of the station building.

The K3 train, which starts in Beijing and travels to Moscow via Ulaanbaatar, is known as the "longest cross-country train in China" . Most of the passengers on this train are tourists from all over the world who are eager to explore the scenery along the Siberian railway.

In the next four hours, passengers will undergo border checks, train transfers and leave China at 1 a.m. in the confined space, according to several travel advisories.

I followed them into a convenience store in the terminal where they were about to exchange Tugrik, the currency of Mongolia, when several border inspectors stopped them and passengers who had entered the bathroom were cleared, "please go back to your cars and wait. "

The flight attendant replied more bluntly: "probably not. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The train passes through the distant snow field, but still can not completely leave the illness cloud. / Credit:

January 22,2100 hours

The air in the K3 train seemed to freeze

The tense breath that shakes nerve, begin to spread from 22 pm about 15:30.

At that time, the train is to the junction of Jin and Mongolia, the carriage door suddenly wafted a strong smell of vinegar, "the train has three Wuhan passengers, " the news from those water basin spread by the crew.

And as we suspiciously climbed onto the train one by one from the Erlian Platform, the border agents, with their temperature monitors, poked each other's foreheads.

Soon, the tension in the carriage escalated after a "one person has fever" warning. The passenger that leans in the window edge rests, all put on a mask by chance.

A few hours earlier, K3 passengers had exchanged lighthearted lessons about playing pestilence and checking to see if their cities had fallen.

Also a few hours ago, there was no visible new pneumonia screening campaign at the Beijing Railway Station, which was built in the Guangxu era and will remain under pressure from the annual Spring Festival travel rush until Jan. 22,2020.

The air seemed to freeze. The carriage is cut into two parallel spaces: A girl on a group outing turns over a Board Game Card, "werewolves! Werewolves! " guffaws through the walls, there are passengers with a rich meaning of the word "cool" to describe the immediate situation, books, mobile phones, pad under the cover of how much the eyebrows and eyes out of anxiety.

A Mongolia girl who worked in Beijing later said she had wanted to visit Zamyn-d's relatives and "relax" on the grasslands, but now worried that trains would be restricted from leaving the country and "repatriated" to Beijing, are you facing the possibility of isolation or worse.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Snow-covered stations along the way

During the more than three hours that the K3 train was stuck on the tracks "waiting for the result" , the clock outside the window in the station played the full hour of "the eastern red" and the sporadic sound of firecrackers in the distance crossed each other, a sense of insecurity began to manifest itself in the MINUTIAE of the carriage:

Lines began to form in front of the regularly closed toilet doors, and phones piled up in aisles waiting to be recharged turned red before being "rescued" 

Several passengers sought the so-called "clean feeling" by trying to wash their hands with unheated drinking water from a tea stove

Ambulances are said to be visible from the windows on the side of the platform, but only at the "allegedly" stage.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The train goes through the forest

January 22,22:30

"It will be more difficult to take the danger out of the country. "

Xiao Lu, the conductor in charge of my compartment, said that the situation on the train was being reported to the railway administration, the Health Commission and other relevant departments, there must be a clear way to deal with it before it can enter the track change process.

But as a railroad worker in China's borderlands, he has as limited information as we do, "after the trip, I was told to pay attention to this matter. Now I can only wait and see the result. Of course, if something happens, it has already happened, " said Lu.

He kept using "nothing" to calm people around him, and when a passenger offered to put a mask on him, he said "I don't want to cause panic. ".

He kept swiping his phone while chatting with Lu. The move was unusual for a flight attendant who had to hand over her phone while at work. "The master was kind enough, " she said. "Our job is too difficult. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The view out the window may be fresh enough for passengers, but it is more or less drab in the eyes of the crew. / Credit:

During the decade that accompanied the 1996 German-made coal-powered "original green leather vehicle" -- Foshan K3 -- coal was added, ice was shoveled, sanitation was cleaned, border inspection was carried out by Chinese, Mongolian and Russian workers, and even the immediate order was maintained, said Lu, it's his job.

He has tried "Saunas" in airless cramped compartments in the summer, and has seen snow and sand pile up in the passageways in extreme weather.

He believes that nearly a month's rest after the mission is over is not enough to make up for the 13-day round trip. As for the "poetic and far-off" symbol -- the Parkland, forest and Lake Baikal -- He was even more impressed by the-40-degree temperatures and the persistent lack of signals.

"Isn't it time to watch Xu Zheng's lost mom? There's GonNa be a lot of people like you paying for it. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The chaos of the K 3 car in the movie awkward. / The movie Mama Jon

While listening to Lu, the K3 passenger instinctively puts his experience into the context of a new type of pneumonia, and after several exchanges of views, a preliminary conclusion emerges -- that the equipment is as old as the hills, the limited cleanliness of the train is a potential breeding ground for disease, and the vast geographic spread of the train significantly increases the uncertainty of travel, but the cold wind at the junction of the train car can still keep the air flowing.

"It's better than high-speed trains, airlock space. "

"Let's just say K3 has seen all kinds of situations, including the current one. But taking the threat out of the country is even more troubling. Immediate restrictions are actually the most effective way to do it. "

An elderly conductor who called the train robbery in the 1990s "just like in the TV series" exclaimed.

At 23:43, the train suddenly began to move, like a burst of a dull and exciting cough, slowly into the transfer workshop. Seven passengers from Hubei Province and those with a recent history of visits have confirmed that they were advised to get off the bus and enter the Erenhot for quarantine.

Friends later told me that this included a Chongqing passenger who shared a compartment with three Wuhan passengers, while a girl working and living in another province had to give up her passport because it was issued in Hubei Province.

I have heard two very different versions of the fate of the seven "deactivated" passengers.

The conductor from the train next door said: "The fever of 37 degrees 3, has been strictly dealt with. In fact, all good, not a big problem. "

But Xiaodeng learned from a group of "Donkey Friends" that the wuhan-born passengers with fever had been isolated as suspected cases and that the remaining six people, although living together, could not leave the dormitory.

The remaining passengers are not sure whether they had contact with the three Wuhan passengers in the dining car or other places, discussions like, "can you stop running around? " And "really don't want to be in the news? " Began Rolling in the car.

The impact from the bottom of the train becomes the only source of positive energy when the train changes tracks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A long timetable

January 23rd, 13:30 noon

"How can you be sure? Have a bottle of vodka. Sterilize it. "

At 3:53 am on the 23rd, the K3 train left the Erenhot port and plunged into Mongolia's vast Gobi desert after being checked, registered, notified and advised to return, the Great Gate marked "the People's Republic of China" began to recede into the darkness behind it.

The whole process of screening and registration took about seven hours.

By the time the Mongolian border guards at Zamenude station boarded the train, isolation suits, goggles, 3MN95 masks and latex gloves had appeared at the door of the compartment, which had not been seen for 17 years.

"Hurry! " was repeated three times in Chinese as the card and passport were handed to the other party, more than an hour after the news that "Wuhan will close the exit from Han at 10:00 on the same day" had appeared on mobile phone feeds.

Charles, a Hong Kong citizen, was seen in the dining car around 13:30 on January 23. He liked to travel by train, and the K3 trip had been on his mind for a while.

"taking the high-speed railway to Beijing also passes through Wuhan. It seems like a good hero, but is it your word that counts? "

"But it's your word against mine. " That's especially true of the K3 community at the time. Outside the window, the Gobi glows with sunlight. Horses and camels can be seen on the side of the road, as well as the bodies of frozen animals, as if in a snowy country.

Four beijing-accented passengers in the dining car opened a bottle of vodka. "What's the use of wearing a mask? If you really want to be diagnosed, you can run away with it. Have a bottle of vodka and sterilize it. "

January 25,10:10

From "unexpected misfortune" to "Buddhism talks and laughs"

On January 25, at 10:10, I received a message from my cabin mate, a Zi: "I saw the news paper. The Erenhot has been diagnosed. Pay Attention. "

Violet and I parted on the afternoon of the 24th at Irkutsk Station on the shores of Lake Baikal. As the doors opened on the green and white building at Irkutsk station, the air, nearly minus 12 degrees, filled the nasal passages excitingly, as if the confinement had been lifted.

Two Nights and one day before that, we were not allowed to get off the train during the entire journey through Mongolia. The Ulan Bator railway station quarantine officers sprayed disinfectant on the wheels and the garbage cans. In the mongolian-russian border city of Dodrny, the Russian border inspection officers are required to check our personal belongings, but this time just stood at a distance to command our own display.

After I told Ah Zi to take care of herself, I connected to the Internet and read in the news of "People's Daily" that there was a newly confirmed case of new type of pneumonia in Inner Mongolia, bringing the total to 2 cases, to confirm the veracity of this information (a suspected case of Xilingol League Erenhot has been confirmed, the first confirmed case reported to the Xilingol League) .

What is a little unexpected is that if the public opinion prevailing in the "seven hours of terror" on the 22nd is to define the experience of seven passengers being "persuaded to leave" at the border as a "sudden and unexpected disaster" , and worried that the advent of such "unexpected disasters" may lead to their own value of thousands of dollars in Russia follow-up itinerary for naught, then the passengers at this time have been reported, isolation as an obligation, the response also appears calm.

Small lights in the "Donkey" group appeared in a post. Originally, that holds the Hubei to issue the passport to be quarantined the girl in a travel forum to post "the distress letter" .

By the afternoon of February 27, the letter had been read more than 50,000 times on Wechat.

The letter described his situation after he got off the bus, using expressions such as "the border of the country in distress" , "compulsory blood tests" , "treating us as prisoners" , "the customs office beat him to death with one shot" and so on, but the comments section "put the big picture first" vehemently refuted.

With this as a mirror, we simply discussed a "approach" : adjust the mentality, frankly accept all arrangements to deal with;

From the 25th, "self-isolation" , as far as possible to reduce travel, no longer go to the dining car to eat, responsible for themselves and others.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
New Year's Eve dinner on a train

In fact, with 22"Fright 7 hours"as a starting point, carriage corridor has been transformed into a"alternative public space".

Passengers are exchanging and sharing, extending from the initial snacks, adapters, and well-connected electronic devices that can be used to receive information online to those "Buddhist chatter and laughter. ". At the same time, people began to call each other by name.

January 25,12:30

The K3, a small boat passing through the eye of the storm

Old Forest, a flight attendant, joined the cast of the film on the afternoon of May 25.

He was squinting at the door of the box, trying to see Xu Zheng on the IPAD screen running through the overly neat "K3 box" : "where is this? K3? Fake! How could I not be there? " He sat down in his bunk amid laughter.

This is the first time we've had an open-minded conversation with a flight attendant. Until then, perhaps because of their professionalism, they were too "out of the loop" -- as from the discovery of a case of fever in Wuhan on the evening of the 22nd to the news release of the diagnosis, albeit accompanied by a pronounced facial muscle twitch, and the instant silence of the eye, but from the small land and his master old Jia mouth say "nothing" "broken" "resigned to fate" in, you almost do not feel the obvious emotional ups and downs.

But Lin is not unafraid.

A day before his departure, he was already worried by the deluge of news about the new pneumonia. He took several sips of wine, only to be shocked when he saw the "visibly disfigured" heated woman being led out of the carriage.

It was the only sterilization he could think of at the moment.

According to his recollection, colleagues did not make special preparations for the trip, the conditions on the bus were limited, the first-aid items at home were not complete, the "protective equipment" he carried with him, or the dozens of masks his daughter gave him before he boarded the bus, and a lucky charm for him from the Lama Temple.

When the amulet was hung around his neck, his daughter said, "Dad, come back safe and sound! "

Compared with high speed rail and bullet trains, the green train has become an extremely marginalized mode of rail travel, Old Forest said. But the K3, which has maintained the traditional friendship between China, Mongolia and Russia since the 1950s, is given special political significance and can not be stopped, even in 2003, "SARS" such a special period, it must also be the normal form of empty start. He wondered, however, why we had to "wander so far away" on the occasion of family reunions.

Passengers back home may face uncomfortable Spring Festival, also mentioned more than ten days of holiday spent on the dinner table, a bit of a pity.

Later, little lamp suddenly exclaimed, people sometimes live much like a soldier in the offensive line, always feel that there are veterans in front of you to bear the danger of bullets, can be wayward or distracted, or even casually blame them, until a moment, before you realize it's empty.

Lam felt the same way.

"My daughter always says that I don't understand young people's lifestyle and there is a generation gap with me. What generation gap do I think, isn't it 'bringing people into the gap' ? "

"Just now, I also learned from you the 'young people's lifestyle' with an open mind. I don't think what the older generation said is necessarily right, but they have all come through hard times and have their own way of thinking about things. Spend more time with them in the future and listen to what they are thinking

When the story refers to her parents'Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps as if in Takovski's childhood, an introverted passenger, Siqi, had suddenly pushed Jankowski, a Soviet actor who had worked with Tarkovsky on nostalgia and the Mirror, to a wall of graffiti on his phone, she said it was her reason for coming to Russia, "I don't know if it will happen. ".

"I used to read Russian and Soviet literature and I used to think that fate was written in an obscure and heavy way. Now I understand it a little bit. But it's not bad to get out of the car and be sent away. First, people have to take care of each other. Second, people have to return to their roots. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Beyond the daisies, the sky lights up outside the car window

Outside the window, the clouds were gathering, and snow was sweeping through the birch forests along the Yenisei River.

It was only at Novosibirsk Main railway station, as I walked along the icy platform, trying to identify my own column from the identical looking carriages, that I suddenly recognized cocoa's bouquet of daisies by the window.

After all that time, they're still alive and well.
